? Strive in their service","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 31, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Amr reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, asking permission to wage jihad. The Prophet said, \u201cAre your parents alive?\u201d The man said yes. The Prophet said, \u201cThen strive in the service of them both.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3004, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2549\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":1015,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/08\/30\/deeds-intention-niyyah-ikhlaas\/","url_meta":{"origin":28475,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Niyyah: Deeds only rewarded by their intentions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 30, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, deeds are only with intentions, and every person will have only what they intended. Whoever emigrated to Allah and His Messenger, his emigration is for Allah and His Messenger. Whoever emigrated to get something\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":1921,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/02\/03\/hijrah-emigration-hasanat\/","url_meta":{"origin":28475,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hijrah: Allah accepts good deeds wherever you are","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa'id reported: A bedouin came to the Prophet and asked him about emigration. The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Woe to you! The matter of emigration is difficult. Have you got some camels?\" The man said yes. The Prophet said, \"Do you pay its charity?\" The\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":1926,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/02\/04\/hijrah-not-wajib-no-fitnah\/","url_meta":{"origin":28475,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hijrah: No obligatory emigration after end of persecution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"'Ata bin Abi Rabah reported: I visited Aisha, may Allah be pleased with her, with 'Ubayd bin 'Umayr to ask her about emigration. Aisha said, \u201cThere is no emigration today. One of the believers would flee with his religion to Allah Almighty and to his messenger, peace and blessings be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":951,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/07\/30\/muslim-ho-harm-hijrah\/","url_meta":{"origin":28475,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Islam: Muslims do not harm others, and abandon sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah bin Amr reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"The Muslim is one from whose tongue and hand Muslims are safe. The emigrant\u00a0is the one who abandons what Allah has forbidden.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 10,\u00a0S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 40 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6859,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/21\/virtues-prayer-parents-jihad\/","url_meta":{"origin":28475,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Virtues: Prayer, goodness to parents, jihad","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 21, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: I asked, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, which deed is best?\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPrayer in its proper time.\u201d I asked, \u201cWhat is next?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cGood treatment of\u00a0your parents.\u201d I said, \u201cWhat is next?\u201d The Prophet said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/28475","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=28475"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/28475\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=28475"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=28475"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=28475"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}